01:33:07,444 --> 01:33:10,414
分不清他是誰  不過肯定是我們的人
Can't tell who it is, but he's one of ours.

1136
01:33:11,184 --> 01:33:13,344
我得在外面先吐一會兒
I had to go outside to throw up.

1137
01:33:14,984 --> 01:33:17,614
瞧瞧他們都對這可憐的傢伙 做了些什麼
Look what they did to the poor son-of-a-bitch.

1138
01:34:32,134 --> 01:34:33,494
酋長 你沒事吧?
You okay, Chief?

1139
01:34:34,064 --> 01:34:35,554
別把這事放在心上
Just let it go.

1140
01:34:36,104 --> 01:34:39,094
如果這樣還橇不開他們的錢包 我就沒招了
If that doesn't pry open their wallets, nothing will.

1141
01:34:47,584 --> 01:34:49,574
老天爺  他喝醉了
Jesus Christ, he's drunk.

1142
01:34:54,184 --> 01:34:55,784
該死的印第安人
Goddamn Indians.

1143
01:35:06,964 --> 01:35:09,094
來 酋長 我們回家
Come on, Chief. Let's get you home.

1144
01:35:14,494 --> 01:35:17,794
戰士體育場：獻給服役的人們


1145
01:35:19,044 --> 01:35:22,574
我聽到的可不是這樣 我問過一圈了 我又不蠢
That's not what I hear. I called around, I'm not stupid.

1146
01:35:22,644 --> 01:35:24,644
他從一開始就喝醉了
He's been drunk since he started this damn tour,

1147
01:35:24,714 --> 01:35:26,444
純粹譁眾取寵
making a spectacle of himself.

1148
01:35:26,524 --> 01:35:29,814
居然還在接待宴會上摟著那個 可憐的女人又哭又嚎
Just about choked that poor woman at the reception, blubbering.

1149
01:35:29,894 --> 01:35:32,554
老天 看看你們手下人的德性
Jesus Christ, you're supposed to be watching these men.

1150
01:35:32,624 --> 01:35:33,684
是 先生
Yes, sir.

1151
01:35:33,764 --> 01:35:35,954
他讓我們看起來就像個笨蛋
Well, he's making us look like regular asses.

1152
01:35:36,024 --> 01:35:37,054
我絕無冒犯之意 長官
Well, with all due respect, sir,

1153
01:35:37,134 --> 01:35:39,154
他一開始就不想做這次巡迴籌款
he never wanted to come on this trip in the first place.

1154
01:35:39,234 --> 01:35:41,634
（當時）他又踢又打 大喊大叫 我們好不容易才把他從船上拉下來
We had to pull him, kicking and screaming, off that boat.

1155
01:35:41,704 --> 01:35:43,694
他想跟他的戰友在一起
He wants to be with his unit.

1156
01:35:43,774 --> 01:35:46,464
他還有什麼戰友？ 全他媽死了
What unit? They're all fucking dead.

1157
01:35:47,104 --> 01:35:50,774
他就是靠喝酒嘔吐 來紀念他們的麼？
This is how he honors those men? By drinking and throwing up, and...

1158
01:35:50,844 --> 01:35:53,504
他不是想回去麼？ 好 我們就讓他回去
You know what? He wants it, great, we'll send him back.

1159
01:35:53,584 --> 01:35:57,534
叫他收拾好行李 搭今天的火車走人 他不配穿上這身制服！
Get him packed and on a train today. He's an embarrassment to the uniform.

1160
01:35:58,914 --> 01:36:00,254
是 先生
Yes, sir.

1161
01:36:07,294 --> 01:36:08,694
交給我做
I'll do it.

1162
01:36:28,184 --> 01:36:31,614
好啊 不 其實… 很好 我就是那麼想的
Yeah, no, that's... That's good. That's what I want.

1163
01:36:33,954 --> 01:36:35,684
我知道那是好事
I know it's a good thing,

1164
01:36:36,554 --> 01:36:39,784
巡迴籌款 因為我們需要錢
raising the money and that, 'cause we need it.

1165
01:36:42,194 --> 01:36:43,254
但是
But,

1166
01:36:44,064 --> 01:36:46,894
我受不了別人叫我英雄
I can't take them calling me a hero.

1167
01:36:48,964 --> 01:36:51,804
我所做的不過是努力不被打中
All I did was try not to get shot.

1168
01:36:57,174 --> 01:37:00,144
我見過的
Some of the things I saw done,

1169
01:37:00,214 --> 01:37:02,044
還有做過的事
things I did,

1170
01:37:03,854 --> 01:37:07,184
沒什麼可自豪的 你明白麼？
they weren't things to be proud of, you know?

1171
01:37:17,194 --> 01:37:18,254
麥克…
Mike...

1172
01:37:22,734 --> 01:37:24,824
麥克才是英雄
Mike was a hero.

1173
01:37:28,174 --> 01:37:29,834
你見過他麼？
You ever meet him?

1174
01:37:31,974 --> 01:37:33,004
沒有
No.

1175
01:37:39,184 --> 01:37:41,084
他是我見過最好的陸戰隊員
Best Marine I ever met.

1176
01:37:46,124 --> 01:37:50,084
酋長 我覺得 如果是麥克 而不是你坐在這堛爾
You know, Chief, I think if Mike was sitting here instead of you

1177
01:37:51,564 --> 01:37:54,094
他也會這麼評價自己的
he'd be saying the same thing about himself,

1178
01:37:56,134 --> 01:37:57,894
說自己不是英雄
not being a hero.

1179
01:38:05,114 --> 01:38:06,304
可能吧
Maybe.

1180
01:38:08,144 --> 01:38:11,044
他是個好人
He was a good guy.

1181
01:38:12,054 --> 01:38:14,884
但我覺得 他看到我現在的樣子以後
But I think that he would be ashamed of me,

1182
01:38:16,654 --> 01:38:18,784
會替我感到丟人的
seeing me the way I am.

1183
01:38:37,944 --> 01:38:41,884
回去之前我能看看我媽媽麼
Think I could see my ma before they ship me off?

1184
01:38:43,284 --> 01:38:45,804
就一眼 行麼 看看媽媽
Think they'd do that? See my ma?

1185
01:38:50,824 --> 01:38:52,344
抱歉 艾拉
I'm sorry, Ira.

1186
01:39:04,304 --> 01:39:07,504
你跟她的孩子們就這麼說
We got stories now to tell our kids, I guess.

1187
01:39:07,574 --> 01:39:09,334
保持低調
Keep your head down.

1188
01:39:18,984 --> 01:39:20,544
發車
All aboard.

1189
01:39:20,624 --> 01:39:22,014
好運 酋長
Good luck, Chief.

1190
01:39:54,324 --> 01:39:56,784
在那之後我見過他一次
I think I saw him once after that.

1191
01:39:56,854 --> 01:39:59,844
大概是在戰後六七年吧
It was maybe six or seven years after the war.

1192
01:39:59,924 --> 01:40:02,984
我當時是推銷員 經常開車
I was working as a salesman, doing a lot of driving.

1193
01:40:03,064 --> 01:40:04,894
有次我向西橫穿得克薩斯
I was driving west across Texas.

1194
01:40:04,964 --> 01:40:07,864
當時一心想回家 正找方向呢
I was just trying to get where I was going so I could get home.

1195
01:40:07,934 --> 01:40:10,694
然後我看到他 在路邊想搭車
And I saw this guy hitchhiking on the side of the road.

1196
01:40:10,774 --> 01:40:14,104
一瞬間 我想到可能是他
And, for a second, I thought it might've been him.

1197
01:40:18,514 --> 01:40:22,104
我現在經常後悔當時 為什麼不停下來 但我當時很急
I always regret that I didn't stop, but I was in a hurry.

1198
01:40:23,214 --> 01:40:25,204
而且他是個印第安人
And he was an Indian.

1199
01:40:25,284 --> 01:40:27,844
我們總對報紙說 當時艾拉執意
We always told the press that Ira insisted

1200
01:40:27,924 --> 01:40:30,284
要回部隊繼續戰鬥
that he was going back to fight with his unit

1201
01:40:30,354 --> 01:40:33,724
這至少算是部分真實的吧
which was at least partially true, but

1202
01:40:35,994 --> 01:40:38,224
但最後報紙頭條出來卻不是這樣
that isn't what got the headlines.

1203
01:40:38,934 --> 01:40:40,594
我們訂婚了
We're engaged.

1204
01:40:44,904 --> 01:40:46,604
我失陪一會兒 親愛的
Excuse me a minute, darling.

1205
01:40:46,674 --> 01:40:48,804
嘿 醫生? 嗯?
Hey, Doc? Yeah?

1206
01:40:48,874 --> 01:40:50,964
有時間麼? 嗯
Got a minute? Yeah.

1207
01:40:51,044 --> 01:40:53,014
車上見
I'll see you at the car.

1208
01:40:54,414 --> 01:40:57,814
你聽說過我就要結婚了麼？ 聽說了 瑞尼 那太好了
You hear I'm getting married? I did, Rene. That's great.

1209
01:40:59,554 --> 01:41:03,424
是啊 她要求的 她等了我這麼久
Yeah, it's something she wants. She waited for me all this time.

1210
01:41:04,524 --> 01:41:07,584
她還不習慣這一切 但她可是個好女孩
She's not used to all this, but she's a good girl.

1211
01:41:07,664 --> 01:41:09,724
我確定你會很幸福的
I'm sure you'll be very happy.

1212
01:41:10,264 --> 01:41:13,164
我在考慮是不是請你當我的伴郎
So, I was wondering if you'd be my best man.

1213
01:41:13,264 --> 01:41:14,294
我？
Me?

1214
01:41:16,364 --> 01:41:21,234
你在家奡N沒有什麼人麼？ 比如叫一個兄弟來當？
Don't you have somebody at home, a buddy, you'd rather ask?

1215
01:41:21,674 --> 01:41:23,764
嗯  不太多
Well, I didn't really make many.

1216
01:41:23,844 --> 01:41:27,974
他們不能去是因為… 嗯 我基本沒怎麼跟他們說過話
The ones who didn't go, it's... Well, it's hard to even talk to them.

1217
01:41:28,044 --> 01:41:29,274
知道麼？
You know?

1218
01:41:29,344 --> 01:41:30,744
哦 知道了
Yeah, I know.

1219
01:41:33,984 --> 01:41:35,754
我…我很榮幸
I'd be proud to.

1220
01:41:36,654 --> 01:41:37,984
謝謝
Thank you.

1221
01:41:39,224 --> 01:41:41,994
我得馬上把她拉走 要不然她可能會說
I better go drag her away from them before she announces

1222
01:41:42,064 --> 01:41:45,524
我會成為通用汽車公司老總 什麼的
I'm gonna be president of General Motors or something.

1223
01:41:46,134 --> 01:41:47,364
好的
All right.

1224
01:41:47,434 --> 01:41:50,694
祝賀你 非常感謝  謝謝
Congratulations. Thank you so much. Thank you.

1225
01:41:50,774 --> 01:41:52,364
瑞尼 你真幸運
Rene, you're a lucky man.

1226
01:42:02,584 --> 01:42:04,744
笑一笑 蓋格南先生 說茄子
Big smile, Mrs. Gagnon! Say cheese!

1227
01:42:06,084 --> 01:42:08,684
我沒法抱怨 因為媒體喜歡他們
I couldn't complain because the press loved them,

1228
01:42:08,754 --> 01:42:12,284
相關報道越多 軍債賣得越好
so they wrote more articles and people bought more bonds.

1229
01:42:15,464 --> 01:42:18,924
巡迴籌款還在繼續 只剩下了瑞尼和你父親
The tour went on with just Rene and your dad.

1230
01:42:23,474 --> 01:42:27,424
真正的英雄是那些 沒能從硫磺島活著回來的人們
And the true heroes are the men who didn't make it home from lwo Jima,

1231
01:42:28,044 --> 01:42:31,404
是那些死在硫磺島戰役 和其他戰役中的人們
the men who died at lwo Jima and in other campaigns.

1232
01:42:32,274 --> 01:42:35,144
購買更多的戰爭債券吧
We ask that you honor the memory of those men

1233
01:42:35,214 --> 01:42:37,744
我們將籍此告慰戰歿者的亡靈 萬眾一心 贏得這場戰爭
by buying the war bonds and helping us to win this war.

1234
01:42:38,954 --> 01:42:40,314
謝謝
Thank you.

1235
01:42:44,324 --> 01:42:47,764
一個城市接著一個城市 這鬼差事沒完沒了
City after city, I thought the damn thing'd never end.

1236
01:42:48,664 --> 01:42:52,864
「照片是當時拍的」的流言 也開始流傳
And this rumor kept going around that the photograph had been staged.

1237
01:42:55,064 --> 01:42:56,394
我記得你爸爸告訴他們
I remember your dad telling them

1238
01:42:56,464 --> 01:42:58,404
說他也很想知道 是誰拍了那張照片
that he wished he'd known he was having his picture taken

1239
01:42:58,474 --> 01:43:00,934
他說他就算挖地三尺 也要把拍照人找出來
because he would've ducked the hell out of it.

1240
01:43:01,004 --> 01:43:03,704
當時是誰的主意？ 是誰安排你們擺拍的？
Whose idea was it? Who wanted to stage the thing?

1241
01:43:03,774 --> 01:43:05,264
說說嘛  那是你麼
Come on, it was you?

1242
01:43:05,344 --> 01:43:08,474
照片是擺拍的事是真的麼 醫生？
Was there truth to the rumor that that picture was staged, Doc?

1243
01:43:08,544 --> 01:43:11,014
說吧 醫生? 你能回答那個問題麼?
Come on! Doc? Can you answer that?

1244
01:43:13,154 --> 01:43:17,484
我還記得你爸爸中彈的消息傳過來的情形 當時好像天都要塌下來了
I remember when your dad got shot. All hell was busting loose.

1245
01:43:17,554 --> 01:43:19,584
人們回家看到那張照片以後
People back home saw that picture

1246
01:43:19,654 --> 01:43:23,394
就認為只要我們打下折缽山 就結束了
and thought it was over when we took Suribachi.

1247
01:43:25,164 --> 01:43:26,564
我們那是做夢
We wished.

1248
01:43:27,304 --> 01:43:29,894
當時我們正被壓制
Anyways, we're pinned down.

1249
01:43:29,964 --> 01:43:32,764
迫擊炮 榴彈炮 機槍
Mortars, shells, machine guns.

1250
01:43:33,844 --> 01:43:36,634
子彈 彈片橫飛
Fire coming from every which direction, right?

1251
01:43:37,544 --> 01:43:41,244
然後我們聽到有人喊 「醫務兵倒下了」
And we hear somebody call, "Corpsman down."

1252
01:43:42,714 --> 01:43:44,374
醫務兵倒下了！
Corpsman down!

1253
01:43:51,154 --> 01:43:55,254
他的喉嚨鮮血噴涌 醫生用盡了一切手段
Blood was spurting out of his throat, and Doc was doing everything he could.

1254
01:43:57,534 --> 01:43:59,654
醫務兵向上望著他
And the Corpsman looks up at him

1255
01:44:01,104 --> 01:44:04,464
脖子中彈 九死一生
and he knows what this means, to be shot in the neck.

1256
01:44:05,474 --> 01:44:08,104
他自己應該知道這一點
He knows he's dying, you can see that.

1257
01:44:08,604 --> 01:44:09,904
但是
But still

1258
01:44:11,374 --> 01:44:15,504
他的眼堨是祈求 祈求醫生能救他一命
in his eyes, he's pleading with Doc to save his life.

1259
01:44:21,824 --> 01:44:23,344
但是醫生無能為力
And Doc can't.

1260
01:45:01,264 --> 01:45:03,854
醫生 你沒事吧? 嗯 我沒事
You okay, Doc? Yeah, I'm fine.

1261
01:45:05,134 --> 01:45:08,294
這還叫沒事 沒什麼大事
Yeah, you look fine. I'm okay.

1262
01:45:08,364 --> 01:45:11,734
趴著別動 我去給你找擔架來
Keep down, all right? I'm gonna go get a stretcher.

1263
01:45:11,804 --> 01:45:12,894
好
Okay.

1264
01:45:20,244 --> 01:45:22,544
醫務兵 醫務兵！
Corpsman. Corpsman!

1265
01:45:23,514 --> 01:45:25,714
看在上帝面上！ 醫務兵！
For God sake, Corpsman!

1266
01:45:45,474 --> 01:45:46,734
醫務兵?
Corpsman?

1267
01:45:49,174 --> 01:45:50,164
醫務兵
Corpsman.

1268
01:45:52,014 --> 01:45:53,804
炮彈來襲！
Incoming!

1269
01:45:57,784 --> 01:45:59,114
讓我看看
Let me see.

1270
01:46:02,254 --> 01:46:05,314
沒那麼糟糕 你會沒事的
It's not that bad. You're gonna be okay. All right?

1271
01:46:05,394 --> 01:46:07,414
堅持住 看著我
Just stay with me. Look at me.

1272
01:46:08,224 --> 01:46:12,184
後來我們花了半小時才找到你爸 他差點流血過多而死
Took us a half-hour to find your dad. He could've bled to death.

1273
01:46:12,264 --> 01:46:13,594
放下
Coming down.

1274
01:46:20,574 --> 01:46:21,764
謝謝
Thanks.

1275
01:46:26,214 --> 01:46:30,614
老兵可能會告訴你說他們是如何 自己中彈  但卻不想拋棄戰友的
Vets'll tell you about being hit but not wanting to leave their buddies.

1276
01:46:31,414 --> 01:46:33,044
通常講 他們都是在撒謊
Usually, they're lying.

1277
01:46:33,754 --> 01:46:36,584
隨便找個理由你就能 拍屁股走人
You'll take any excuse to get out of there.

1278
01:46:37,654 --> 01:46:39,184
但當時確實發生了
But it happens.

1279
01:46:41,394 --> 01:46:44,324
你感覺到 自己讓他們失望了
You get the feeling you're letting them down.

1280
01:46:45,634 --> 01:46:48,154
這我從你爸爸臉上就看得出來
I could see that in your dad's face.

1281
01:46:49,634 --> 01:46:53,124
他只想離開 他看夠了這一切
He wanted to go, he'd seen enough.

1282
01:46:54,844 --> 01:46:56,834
但他不想扔下我們
But he didn't want to leave us.

1283
01:46:58,974 --> 01:47:01,464
你爸爸 真的是一個大好人
Now, he was a hell of a good man, your dad.

1284
01:47:04,954 --> 01:47:06,044
是啊
Yeah.

1285
01:47:06,554 --> 01:47:10,584
我們坐在海灘上的時候 聽到了巨大的轟鳴聲
While we were sitting there on the beach, we heard this great roar.

1286
01:47:10,654 --> 01:47:12,124
於是我們抬頭看
And we looked up.

1287
01:47:17,764 --> 01:47:21,354
那是第一架降落在硫磺島上的 飛機 後來還有幾千架次
That was the first of thousands of landings on lwo.

1288
01:47:21,434 --> 01:47:23,234
看看 嗯
Look at that. Yeah.

1289
01:47:23,874 --> 01:47:25,424
怎麼樣
How about that.

1290
01:47:31,644 --> 01:47:33,164
我一會在回來 好麼
I'm gonna head back, all right?

1291
01:47:33,244 --> 01:47:34,404
好運
Good luck.

1292
01:47:37,554 --> 01:47:40,144
拿下那座島 我們就可以少死很多人 （指提前結束戰爭）
That island saved a lot of lives.

1293
01:47:43,794 --> 01:47:45,554
很多很多人
A lot of lives.

1294
01:47:49,764 --> 01:47:51,924
我沒什麼可說的了
I don't know what else to tell you.

1295
01:48:00,804 --> 01:48:04,434
巡迴籌款結束以後 我爸終於可以做手術
After the bond tour my dad finally got his operation.

1296
01:48:15,884 --> 01:48:18,914
他回家的時候 戰爭已經結束了
By the time he got home the war was over.

1297
01:48:22,994 --> 01:48:25,824
他做的第一件事 就是向我媽求婚
First thing he did was ask my mom to marry him.

1298
01:48:30,234 --> 01:48:33,004
艾拉嘗試著繼續生活 忘掉從前的一切
Ira tried to get on with his life and put it all behind him.


1299
01:48:30,234 --> 01:48:33,004
牌子上寫的是：全美印第安人大會

1300
01:48:34,744 --> 01:48:37,144
謝謝大家今天邀請我到這
Thank you for having me here today.

1301
01:48:38,174 --> 01:48:43,044
站在這麼多強大的人面前 令我感到榮耀
It's an honor to be in front of such a strong people.

1302
01:48:46,614 --> 01:48:48,284
因為戰爭
Because of the war

1303
01:48:49,884 --> 01:48:53,254
白人會大大加深對印第安人的瞭解
white men will understand Indians a lot better.

1304
01:48:56,764 --> 01:48:59,284
世界也會變得更加美好
And it's going to be a better world.

1305
01:49:19,414 --> 01:49:21,784
但生活對他另有安排
But life had other plans for him.

1306
01:49:35,334 --> 01:49:38,034
你是…你是他  對麼
You're... You're him, aren't you?

1307
01:49:38,104 --> 01:49:39,764
你就是那個英雄  是麼
You're the hero, right?

1308
01:49:43,714 --> 01:49:46,874
太好了  好  孩子們 去合個影吧
Great. All right, kids, go get your picture taken.

1309
01:49:49,414 --> 01:49:51,474
太好了 太好了
Oh, that's great. That's great.

1310
01:49:51,554 --> 01:49:53,174
好 現在說茄子
All right, now say cheese.

1311
01:49:53,254 --> 01:49:54,514
茄子！
Cheese!

1312
01:49:55,054 --> 01:49:58,954
太好了！好的 嘿  多謝你啊 多謝
That's great! Okay. Hey, thanks a lot. Thanks.

1313
01:49:59,394 --> 01:50:01,624
來吧 那可是個英雄 孩子們
Come on. That's a hero, kids.

1314
01:50:12,974 --> 01:50:16,934
英雄  搬一下這個筐吧 太重了我搬不動
Hero, lift this basket, will you? It's too heavy for me.

1315
01:50:42,404 --> 01:50:45,804
瑞尼試著兌現他在巡迴籌款中 所收到的承諾
Rene tried to take advantage of those offers he'd received on the bond tour.

1316
01:50:45,874 --> 01:50:49,704
是的  G-A-G-N-O-N
Yes. G-A-G-N-O-N.

1317
01:50:50,874 --> 01:50:54,274
對 讀作瑞尼 瑞尼 是的
Right. Pronounced Rene. Rene, yes.

1318
01:50:55,314 --> 01:50:59,644
好的 上星期我就打過電話了 好的 那麼 蓋格南先生
Okay, I actually called last week. Yes. Okay, yes. Mr. Gagnon.

1319
01:51:00,354 --> 01:51:04,284
我已經把你的信息轉給了田納科先生 他會給你打過去的
I gave Mr. Tennack your message. I'm sure he'll call you.

1320
01:51:04,924 --> 01:51:07,054
好的 好的
Okay. All right.

1321
01:51:08,194 --> 01:51:09,284
謝謝
Thank you.

1322
01:51:09,864 --> 01:51:12,054
但他只是昨日英雄了
But he was yesterday's hero.

1323
01:51:12,134 --> 01:51:15,394
他甚至向當地警察局申請工作
He even applied for a job at the local police station.

1324
01:51:17,574 --> 01:51:19,934
他們說他還不合格
They said he wasn't qualified.

1325
01:51:20,004 --> 01:51:22,974
和女友波琳在工廠幹了一段之後 他跳了幾次槽
After working the factory with Pauline he tried a few things

1326
01:51:23,044 --> 01:51:25,704
最後做了看門人終此一生
but spent the rest of his life as a janitor.

1327
01:51:28,244 --> 01:51:29,304
至於艾拉…
But Ira...

1328
01:51:29,384 --> 01:51:31,814
艾拉！有訪客！
Ira! You got a visitor.

1329
01:51:35,184 --> 01:51:37,154
艾拉總能上新聞
Ira always made the news.

1330
01:51:37,894 --> 01:51:40,884
亞利桑那州 馬堿鴝玷勾給謏


1331
01:51:43,694 --> 01:51:47,864
我也不知他何以至此 但有一天他就那麼被釋放了
I could never find out why he did it, but one day Ira just took off.

1332
01:52:31,044 --> 01:52:34,504
他邊走邊攔車走了1300多英里
He walked and hitched over 1,300 miles

1333
01:52:34,584 --> 01:52:36,484
從亞利桑那走到得克薩斯
from Arizona to Texas.

1334
01:52:40,114 --> 01:52:43,414
最後找到了正在田里耕地的 哈倫·布勞克的父親
He found Harlon Block's father working his field.

1335
01:52:43,484 --> 01:52:47,754
他的妻子貝爾一聽到哈倫戰死 的消息 就和他分居了
His wife, Belle, had left him soon after they discovered Harlon died.

1336
01:52:48,594 --> 01:52:52,124
她一直都沒有原諒他 讓自己的兒子上戰場的決定
She never forgave him for letting her son go off to war.

1337
01:53:10,214 --> 01:53:12,244
艾拉告訴了他真相
And Ira told him the truth,

1338
01:53:13,484 --> 01:53:16,684
是他的兒子參與了當時的升旗
that it had been his son who raised the flag with them,

1339
01:53:17,454 --> 01:53:19,484
是他的兒子上了照片
his son in the photograph.

1340
01:53:22,264 --> 01:53:24,954
然後 艾拉只是轉身離去
And then he just turned and walked away.

1341
01:53:26,294 --> 01:53:29,164
雖然對於參與升旗他早已看淡
Though the flag-raising meant nothing to him,

1342
01:53:29,734 --> 01:53:32,894
但他知道對於哈倫一家 這意味著什麼
he somehow knew it would mean everything to them.

1343
01:53:49,084 --> 01:53:50,814
謝謝你打來
Thanks for calling.

1344
01:53:54,924 --> 01:53:57,124
貝爾知道真相之後不久
Just as Belle knew all along.

1345
01:54:06,604 --> 01:54:08,404
媒體也得以知曉
The press soon found out

1346
01:54:08,474 --> 01:54:12,434
打電話給漢克的母親說照片上 沒有她的孩子
and called Hank's mom with the news that it wasn't her son after all.

1347
01:54:25,694 --> 01:54:27,354
他們最後一次見面
The last time they all saw each other

1348
01:54:27,424 --> 01:54:30,824
是在海軍陸戰隊戰爭紀念碑 落成儀式上
was at the unveiling of the Marine Corps War Memorial.

1349
01:54:32,364 --> 01:54:35,894
儘管漢克參與了硫磺島上第一面 美國國旗的升旗儀式
And even though he planted the first flag above lwo Jima,

1350
01:54:35,964 --> 01:54:38,364
他的父母卻沒有被邀請
Hank's mother and father weren't invited.

1351
01:55:15,744 --> 01:55:16,794
艾拉
Ira.

1352
01:55:29,584 --> 01:55:31,314
見到你真好 艾拉
It's good to see you, Ira.

1353
01:55:39,894 --> 01:55:41,734
雕像真不錯
Hell of a statue.

1354
01:55:54,914 --> 01:55:57,904
在那之後不久 有人找到了艾拉
It wasn't long after that that they found Ira.

1355
01:55:58,384 --> 01:56:02,484
報紙上說他死於暴曬（與曝光是同一個詞） 沒有人去驗屍瞭解死因
The papers said he died of exposure. There was no autopsy.

1356
01:56:17,264 --> 01:56:18,894
當時 差不多同一時間
It was about that same time

1357
01:56:18,974 --> 01:56:21,494
一天早晨  我爸爸走進車
when my father got in his car early one morning

1358
01:56:21,574 --> 01:56:24,004
告訴我媽媽說他有事情要做
telling my mom he had something to do.

1359
01:56:30,784 --> 01:56:35,184
他開車去了威斯康星州另一端 伊基的母親所在的的一個鎮子
He drove to a town on the other side of Wisconsin where Iggy's mom lived.

1360
01:56:45,234 --> 01:56:47,424
她獲知兒子的死訊以後
Ever since she heard the news about her son

1361
01:56:47,504 --> 01:56:51,524
她就一直試圖找出她兒子的死因 沒有人告訴她
she'd been trying to find out how he died, and no one would tell her.

1362
01:56:53,804 --> 01:56:56,334
我不知道當時他都對她說了些什麼
I never found out what he told her,

1363
01:56:56,404 --> 01:56:59,634
但是我差不多敢保證她聽到的 不是真相
but I can pretty much guarantee it wasn't the truth.

1364
01:57:01,184 --> 01:57:03,614
我媽媽常常問他什麼讓他惦念
My mother would ask him what was troubling him.

1365
01:57:03,684 --> 01:57:05,274
但他從來不說
He would never say.

1366
01:57:13,124 --> 01:57:16,094
每年快到陣亡將士紀念日的時候
And every year, as it got close to Memorial Day,

1367
01:57:16,164 --> 01:57:19,994
記者們就會打電話來 要採訪我爸爸
the reporters would start calling asking to interview my father.

1368
01:57:21,104 --> 01:57:23,764
不 很抱歉 他正在加拿大釣魚
No, I'm sorry. He's fishing in Canada.

1369
01:57:24,634 --> 01:57:27,034
我們總是統一口徑
We were always instructed to say the same thing.

1370
01:57:27,104 --> 01:57:29,044
好的 謝謝
Okay. Thanks.

1371
01:57:32,374 --> 01:57:34,404
麥克坎德勒先生退休後
When Mr. McCandless retired,

1372
01:57:34,484 --> 01:57:38,144
爸爸買下了他戰後工作過的 一家殯儀館
my father bought the funeral home where he'd worked since coming home.

1373
01:57:38,214 --> 01:57:42,244
從此經營生意 養活家人 終此一生
He spent the rest of his life running the business and raising his family.

1374
01:58:30,364 --> 01:58:33,604
他從來不向我們提戰爭 和升旗的事情
He never spoke about the war or about the flag-raising,

1375
01:58:34,304 --> 01:58:36,294
隻字不提
never told us anything.

1376
01:58:36,644 --> 01:58:40,474
我聽到任何與那有關的事情 已經是在他過世以後了
The first time I heard any of these stories was after he died.

1377
01:58:57,464 --> 01:59:00,434
伊基在哪？老天
Where is he? Oh, God.

1378
01:59:02,634 --> 01:59:04,124
他不在這 爸爸
He's not here, Dad.

1379
01:59:05,204 --> 01:59:06,294
他死了
He died.

1380
01:59:08,544 --> 01:59:10,264
誰？誰死了？
Who? Who died?

1381
01:59:11,674 --> 01:59:12,764
伊基
Iggy.

1382
01:59:14,844 --> 01:59:15,934
伊基
Iggy.

1383
01:59:17,414 --> 01:59:20,904
老天 可憐的伊基
Christ, poor Iggy.

1384
01:59:21,924 --> 01:59:24,384
我好多年沒見他了
I hadn't thought of him for years.

1385
01:59:26,354 --> 01:59:28,724
你是怎麼知道伊基的？
How do you know about Iggy?

1386
01:59:29,264 --> 01:59:32,754
你病倒的時候 喊的是他的名字
You were calling for him, when you collapsed.

1387
01:59:37,834 --> 01:59:40,034
我其實也不是在找伊奇
I wasn't looking for Iggy.

1388
01:59:42,144 --> 01:59:44,004
我是在找你
I was looking for you.

1389
01:59:46,274 --> 01:59:47,764
我想…
I wanted to...

1390
01:59:50,584 --> 01:59:54,714
我想告訴你 我很抱歉 我這個父親做得不夠好
I wanted to tell you I'm sorry I wasn't a better father.

1391
01:59:56,184 --> 01:59:57,914
跟你交流不夠
Talked to you more.

1392
01:59:59,394 --> 02:00:00,654
我只是…
I just...

1393
02:00:04,734 --> 02:00:06,064
我很抱歉
I'm sorry.

1394
02:00:08,164 --> 02:00:09,324
抱歉?
Sorry?

1395
02:00:11,474 --> 02:00:14,264
你是世界上最好的父親
You were the best father a man could have.

1396
02:00:24,144 --> 02:00:28,014
我告訴過你我們游泳的事麼
Did I ever tell you they took us swimming?

1397
02:00:32,454 --> 02:00:33,944
沒有 爸爸
No, Dad.

1398
02:00:35,524 --> 02:00:40,124
我們當時升完旗以後 就下山
After we planted the flag, we came down off the mountain

1399
02:00:41,234 --> 02:00:43,034
他們讓我們游泳
and they let us swim.

1400
02:00:44,534 --> 02:00:47,064
那是最有意思的了
It was the funniest thing.

1401
02:00:47,974 --> 02:00:49,704
所有那些戰鬥都暫時拋到腦後
All this fighting

1402
02:00:50,674 --> 02:00:54,614
我們就跳進水  玩得像孩子…
and we were jumping around in the water like kids.

1403
02:00:57,854 --> 02:01:01,014
我就是這樣來記住伊基的
That's the way I remember Iggy now.

1404
02:01:37,584 --> 02:01:41,324
最後我終於發現 他可能是對的
I finally came to the conclusion that maybe he was right.

1405
02:01:41,394 --> 02:01:44,624
也許本來就沒有英雄
Maybe there's no such thing as heroes.

1406
02:01:44,694 --> 02:01:47,294
也許本來他們就是像我爸爸 一樣的凡人
Maybe there are just people like my dad.

1407
02:01:48,504 --> 02:01:49,994
我也終於明白
I finally came to understand

1408
02:01:50,064 --> 02:01:53,504
為什麼他們受不了被人稱作英雄
why they were so uncomfortable being called heroes.

1409
02:01:54,274 --> 02:01:58,074
英雄是我們創造出來的 我們需要英雄
Heroes are something we create, something we need.

1410
02:02:02,414 --> 02:02:06,714
這樣我們就能夠理解那個 以前讓人感到費解的問題
It's a way for us to understand what is almost incomprehensible,

1411
02:02:06,784 --> 02:02:10,014
就是人們為什麼為我們付出 那麼重大的犧牲
how people could sacrifice so much for us.

1412
02:02:10,654 --> 02:02:12,924
但是對於我的父親和他的弟兄們
But for my dad and these men,

1413
02:02:12,994 --> 02:02:16,224
他們承擔生命危險 甘冒槍林彈雨
the risks they took, the wounds they suffered,

1414
02:02:16,294 --> 02:02:18,494
為的不過是他們的戰友
they did that for their buddies.

1415
02:02:18,994 --> 02:02:22,794
他們為國而戰 但是為友而死
They may have fought for their country, but they died for their friends.

1416
02:02:22,864 --> 02:02:25,634
為了他們那些身前身後 的普通戰友們
For the man in front, for the man beside them.

1417
02:02:26,934 --> 02:02:29,994
如果我們想要真正銘記這些人
And if we wish to truly honor these men,

1418
02:02:30,074 --> 02:02:33,044
就應該還他們以本色
we should remember them the way they really were,

1419
02:02:33,114 --> 02:02:35,444
正如我父親所做的那樣
the way my dad remembered them.

1420
02:03:15,424 --> 02:03:16,854
快過來 醫生
Come on, Doc!

1421
02:04:33,418 --> 02:04:36,851
約翰·佈雷德利 （醫生）


1422
02:04:38,218 --> 02:04:41,851
瑞尼·蓋格南


1423
02:04:43,418 --> 02:04:46,851
艾拉·海耶斯


1424
02:04:48,418 --> 02:04:51,851
凱斯·伊奇


1425
02:04:58,718 --> 02:05:02,151
麥克·考特尼


1426
02:05:03,418 --> 02:05:06,851
拉爾夫·伊格納托斯基（伊基）


1427
02:05:08,718 --> 02:05:12,151
亨利·漢森（漢克）


1428
